verses.text_plain: Now after the death of Joshua it came to pass, that the children of Israel asked the Lord, saying, Who shall go up for us against the Canaanites first, to fight against them?
verses.verse_html: 1Now after the death of Joshua it came to pass, that the children of Israel asked the Lord, saying, Who shall go up for us against the Canaanites first, to fight against them?

tokens.text: it came to pass, that the children

verses.text_plain: And the Lord said, Judah shall go up: behold, I have delivered the land into his hand.
verses.verse_html: 2And the Lord said, Judah shall go up: behold, I have delivered the land into his hand.

verses.text_plain: And Judah said unto Simeon his brother, Come up with me into my lot, that we may fight against the Canaanites; and I likewise will go with thee into thy lot. So Simeon went with him.
verses.verse_html: 3And Judah said unto Simeon his brother, Come up with me into my lot, that we may fight against the Canaanites; and I likewise will go with thee into thy lot. So Simeon went with him.

verses.text_plain: And Judah went up; and the Lord delivered the Canaanites and the Perizzites into their hand: and they slew of them in Bezek ten thousand men.
verses.verse_html: 4And Judah went up; and the Lord delivered the Canaanites and the Perizzites into their hand: and they slew of them in Bezek ten thousand men.

verses.text_plain: And they found Adoni–bezek in Bezek: and they fought against him, and they slew the Canaanites and the Perizzites.
verses.verse_html: 5And they found Adoni–bezek in Bezek: and they fought against him, and they slew the Canaanites and the Perizzites.

verses.text_plain: But Adoni–bezek fled; and they pursued after him, and caught him, and cut off his thumbs and his great toes.
verses.verse_html: 6But Adoni–bezek fled; and they pursued after him, and caught him, and cut off his thumbs and his great toes.

verses.text_plain: And Adoni–bezek said, Threescore and ten kings, having their thumbs and their great toes cut off, gathered their meat under my table: as I have done, so God hath requited me. And they brought him to Jerusalem, and there he died.
verses.verse_html:
7And Adoni–bezek said, Threescore and ten kings, having their thumbs and their great toes cut off, gathered their meat under my table: as I have done, so God hath requited me. And they brought him to Jerusalem, and there he died. ▼
▼ their thumbs…: Heb. the thumbs of their hands and of their feet
 , ▼
▼ gathered: or, gleaned

footnotes.body_text: ▼ their thumbs…: Heb. the thumbs of their hands and of their feet
footnotes.body_html: ▼ their thumbs…: Heb. the thumbs of their hands and of their feet

verses.text_plain: Now the children of Judah had fought against Jerusalem, and had taken it, and smitten it with the edge of the sword, and set the city on fire.
verses.verse_html: 8Now the children of Judah had fought against Jerusalem, and had taken it, and smitten it with the edge of the sword, and set the city on fire.

verses.text_plain: And afterward the children of Judah went down to fight against the Canaanites, that dwelt in the mountain, and in the south, and in the valley.
verses.verse_html:
9And afterward the children of Judah went down to fight against the Canaanites, that dwelt in the mountain, and in the south, and in the valley. ▼
▼ valley: or, low country

footnotes.body_html: ▼ valley: or, low country

verses.text_plain: And Judah went against the Canaanites that dwelt in Hebron: (now the name of Hebron before was Kirjath–arba:) and they slew Sheshai, and Ahiman, and Talmai.
verses.verse_html: 10And Judah went against the Canaanites that dwelt in Hebron: (now the name of Hebron before was Kirjath–arba:) and they slew Sheshai, and Ahiman, and Talmai.

verses.text_plain: And from thence he went against the inhabitants of Debir: and the name of Debir before was Kirjath–sepher:
verses.verse_html: 11And from thence he went against the inhabitants of Debir: and the name of Debir before was Kirjath–sepher:

verses.text_plain: And Caleb said, He that smiteth Kirjath–sepher, and taketh it, to him will I give Achsah my daughter to wife.
verses.verse_html: 12And Caleb said, He that smiteth Kirjath–sepher, and taketh it, to him will I give Achsah my daughter to wife.

tokens.text: it, to him will I give

verses.text_plain: And Othniel the son of Kenaz, Caleb’s younger brother, took it: and he gave him Achsah his daughter to wife.
verses.verse_html: 13And Othniel the son of Kenaz, Caleb’s younger brother, took it: and he gave him Achsah his daughter to wife.

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass, when she came to him, that she moved him to ask of her father a field: and she lighted from off her ass; and Caleb said unto her, What wilt thou?
verses.verse_html: 14And it came to pass, when she came to him, that she moved him to ask of her father a field: and she lighted from off her ass; and Caleb said unto her, What wilt thou?

tokens.text: And it came to pass, when she came

verses.text_plain: And she said unto him, Give me a blessing: for thou hast given me a south land; give me also springs of water. And Caleb gave her the upper springs and the nether springs.
verses.verse_html: 15And she said unto him, Give me a blessing: for thou hast given me a south land; give me also springs of water. And Caleb gave her the upper springs and the nether springs.

verses.text_plain: And the children of the Kenite, Moses’ father in law, went up out of the city of palm trees with the children of Judah into the wilderness of Judah, which lieth in the south of Arad; and they went and dwelt among the people.
verses.verse_html: 16And the children of the Kenite, Moses’ father in law, went up out of the city of palm trees with the children of Judah into the wilderness of Judah, which lieth in the south of Arad; and they went and dwelt among the people.

verses.text_plain: And Judah went with Simeon his brother, and they slew the Canaanites that inhabited Zephath, and utterly destroyed it. And the name of the city was called Hormah.
verses.verse_html: 17And Judah went with Simeon his brother, and they slew the Canaanites that inhabited Zephath, and utterly destroyed it. And the name of the city was called Hormah.

verses.text_plain: Also Judah took Gaza with the coast thereof, and Askelon with the coast thereof, and Ekron with the coast thereof.
verses.verse_html: 18Also Judah took Gaza with the coast thereof, and Askelon with the coast thereof, and Ekron with the coast thereof.

verses.text_plain: And the Lord was with Judah; and he drave out the inhabitants of the mountain; but could not drive out the inhabitants of the valley, because they had chariots of iron.
verses.verse_html:
19And the Lord was with Judah; and he drave out the inhabitants of the mountain; but could not drive out the inhabitants of the valley, because they had chariots of iron. ▼
▼ drave…: or, possessed the mountain

footnotes.body_html: ▼ drave…: or, possessed the mountain

verses.text_plain: And they gave Hebron unto Caleb, as Moses said: and he expelled thence the three sons of Anak.
verses.verse_html: 20And they gave Hebron unto Caleb, as Moses said: and he expelled thence the three sons of Anak.

verses.text_plain: And the children of Benjamin did not drive out the Jebusites that inhabited Jerusalem; but the Jebusites dwell with the children of Benjamin in Jerusalem unto this day.
verses.verse_html: 21And the children of Benjamin did not drive out the Jebusites that inhabited Jerusalem; but the Jebusites dwell with the children of Benjamin in Jerusalem unto this day.

verses.text_plain: And the house of Joseph, they also went up against Beth–el: and the Lord was with them.
verses.verse_html: 22And the house of Joseph, they also went up against Beth–el: and the Lord was with them.

verses.text_plain: And the house of Joseph sent to descry Beth–el. (Now the name of the city before was Luz.)
verses.verse_html: 23And the house of Joseph sent to descry Beth–el. (Now the name of the city before was Luz.)

verses.text_plain: And the spies saw a man come forth out of the city, and they said unto him, Shew us, we pray thee, the entrance into the city, and we will shew thee mercy.
verses.verse_html: 24And the spies saw a man come forth out of the city, and they said unto him, Shew us, we pray thee, the entrance into the city, and we will shew thee mercy.

tokens.text: us, we pray thee, the entrance

verses.text_plain: And when he shewed them the entrance into the city, they smote the city with the edge of the sword; but they let go the man and all his family.
verses.verse_html: 25And when he shewed them the entrance into the city, they smote the city with the edge of the sword; but they let go the man and all his family.

verses.text_plain: And the man went into the land of the Hittites, and built a city, and called the name thereof Luz: which is the name thereof unto this day.
verses.verse_html: 26And the man went into the land of the Hittites, and built a city, and called the name thereof Luz: which is the name thereof unto this day.

verses.text_plain: Neither did Manasseh drive out the inhabitants of Beth–shean and her towns, nor Taanach and her towns, nor the inhabitants of Dor and her towns, nor the inhabitants of Ibleam and her towns, nor the inhabitants of Megiddo and her towns: but the Canaanites would dwell in that land.
verses.verse_html: 27Neither did Manasseh drive out the inhabitants of Beth–shean and her towns, nor Taanach and her towns, nor the inhabitants of Dor and her towns, nor the inhabitants of Ibleam and her towns, nor the inhabitants of Megiddo and her towns: but the Canaanites would dwell in that land.

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass, when Israel was strong, that they put the Canaanites to tribute, and did not utterly drive them out.
verses.verse_html: 28And it came to pass, when Israel was strong, that they put the Canaanites to tribute, and did not utterly drive them out.

tokens.text: And it came to pass, when Israel

verses.text_plain: Neither did Ephraim drive out the Canaanites that dwelt in Gezer; but the Canaanites dwelt in Gezer among them.
verses.verse_html: 29Neither did Ephraim drive out the Canaanites that dwelt in Gezer; but the Canaanites dwelt in Gezer among them.

verses.text_plain: Neither did Zebulun drive out the inhabitants of Kitron, nor the inhabitants of Nahalol; but the Canaanites dwelt among them, and became tributaries.
verses.verse_html: 30Neither did Zebulun drive out the inhabitants of Kitron, nor the inhabitants of Nahalol; but the Canaanites dwelt among them, and became tributaries.

verses.text_plain: Neither did Asher drive out the inhabitants of Accho, nor the inhabitants of Zidon, nor of Ahlab, nor of Achzib, nor of Helbah, nor of Aphik, nor of Rehob:
verses.verse_html: 31Neither did Asher drive out the inhabitants of Accho, nor the inhabitants of Zidon, nor of Ahlab, nor of Achzib, nor of Helbah, nor of Aphik, nor of Rehob:

verses.text_plain: But the Asherites dwelt among the Canaanites, the inhabitants of the land: for they did not drive them out.
verses.verse_html: 32But the Asherites dwelt among the Canaanites, the inhabitants of the land: for they did not drive them out.

tokens.text: for they did not drive them out

verses.text_plain: Neither did Naphtali drive out the inhabitants of Beth–shemesh, nor the inhabitants of Beth–anath; but he dwelt among the Canaanites, the inhabitants of the land: nevertheless the inhabitants of Beth–shemesh and of Beth–anath became tributaries unto them.
verses.verse_html: 33Neither did Naphtali drive out the inhabitants of Beth–shemesh, nor the inhabitants of Beth–anath; but he dwelt among the Canaanites, the inhabitants of the land: nevertheless the inhabitants of Beth–shemesh and of Beth–anath became tributaries unto them.

verses.text_plain: And the Amorites forced the children of Dan into the mountain: for they would not suffer them to come down to the valley:
verses.verse_html: 34And the Amorites forced the children of Dan into the mountain: for they would not suffer them to come down to the valley:

verses.text_plain: But the Amorites would dwell in mount Heres in Aijalon, and in Shaalbim: yet the hand of the house of Joseph prevailed, so that they became tributaries.
verses.verse_html:
35But the Amorites would dwell in mount Heres in Aijalon, and in Shaalbim: yet the hand of the house of Joseph prevailed, so that they became tributaries. ▼
▼ prevailed: Heb. was heavy

footnotes.body_html: ▼ prevailed: Heb. was heavy

verses.text_plain: And the coast of the Amorites was from the going up to Akrabbim, from the rock, and upward.
verses.verse_html:
36And the coast of the Amorites was from the going up to Akrabbim, from the rock, and upward. ▼
